			<td align="left" valign="top" background="/images/necrotableheader1.gif">
				<font width="100%" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" size="2" color=white><b>HOW TO: Kill the WC Druids from 34-39</b>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr bgcolor="black">
			<td align="left" valign="top" valign="top">
				<font face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" size="2" color=white>
				written by <b>Azumaan Necromaan</b> on <b>3/12/2003 8:51:16 AM</b>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr bgcolor="#37437B">
			<td align="left" valign="top" valign="top">
				<font face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" size="2" color=white><blockquote><br>
				34-39: WC Druids.<br><br>Here's how to flawlessly kill the druids:<br><br>Here's my spell lineup:<br>1) LifeTap<br>2) Snare<br>3) Interchangeable (CoB, Pet, Dispell [<-- not necessary])<br>4) Venom of the Snake<br>5) Vampiric Curse<br>6) Invoke Fear<br>7) Pet Buff<br>8) Feign Death<br><br>***SETUP***<br><br>When you first log on, there will be 2 druids up. Summon a pet and buff him (only need haste).<br>I usually set up camp near one of the trees, nearest the wizard spires and on the bottom of the hill (there are two in that area, get near the one closest to the lake) <br><br>By positioning yourself here, you will always get the left druid when you hit F8 (unless a newbie mobs paths across you and interrupts your F8 targeting, just let it walk by)<br><br>Copy and Paste this link to see how to best position yourself:<br>http://baadan.freewebspace.com/WCdruidsSetUp.JPG<br><br>***THE FIGHT***<br>--Target the Druid on the right (Druid A)<br>--Send pet on Druid A<br>--Hit F8 to target Druid B (the one on the left)<br>--Cast Invoke Fear on Druid B<br>--Cast Venom of the Snake on Druid A<br>--Cast Invoke Fear on Druid A<br>--Cast AoB/CoB on yourself, then VC on Druid B<br>--Sit down and watch the mana flow and your pet tear up the druid.<br>--Once Druid A dies, DON'T kill Druid B right away, chances are, fear already broke, when that happens, simply fear Druid B off, he will path towards the lake and give you a few min to recoup and more importanly, *space out the spawn.*<br><br>Loot up and sell to that very forgiving Slea Pinewhisper on the other side of the rings.<br><br>Now that they are split - it gets EASY. As soon as a druid pops, hit F8 to target, send pet (who you make sure to keep hasted), stand up, Fear it, cast VoS, then sit down. Yep, that's it. I lose about 15% of my mana bar doing this (240mana) and I can have it medded back up to 100% before the fight ends (without any kind of lich or chanter spell, plain ol' Meditation)<br><br>***PERSONAL NOTES***<br><br>If my HP is a little low, I cast VC, draining me another 144 mana, and if I don't need TOO much HP back, I'll hit my Words of Darkness for AoD, but if I need a lot of HP, I'll just med the old fashioned way. After about 2 minutes that druid will be dead and you can 9 times out of 10 be medded back up to 100% all around (your hp, your mana, and pet hp) before the next druid pops. They are on a (I beleive) 6 minute or so spawn timer.<br><br>***TIPS***<br>--When they first pop, they will begin to cast a Skin like XXX spell. Don't worry. They are druids, VoS + hasted pet still = dead druid, even when they are fully buffed (like when you first log on and they've had time to buff themselves) they are still easy.<br>--The Skin spell takes a good 4 sec or so to cast, and guess what - Fear doens't interrupt the spell and your pet probably won't either.<br>This is a GOOD thing :)<br>This gives you 4 or so seconds of FREE time!!<br>The druid pops, begins casting, you send pet in, you cast Invoke Fear and Druid gets feared about the same time the pet gets there, the druid finishes casting the spell (not sure whether or not the druid gets the benefits from the spell but I would assume so) then takes off running into a really nice fear pattern (trust me, you wont believe how perfect it is ;)) If you go quickly, you can have the druid feared, VoSed and sicked on by the pet all before it bounces the first time from the odd fear pathing. Sit down and you will be back at 100% mana when the fight ends.<br>--Darkness is NOT, and I repeat NOT necessary here. I only have it memmed for the odd time when Fear breaks early on the second druid (Druid B) and I have to fear it off and then when it comes back and I re-fear to start killing it, it starts running off at SoW speed so I snare it so the pet can keep up with it.<br>&nbsp;<br>
			</td>
